cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the comparison of Bluetooth mesh with information-centric networking (ICN) in the context of IoT. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the design decisions and performance of both architectures, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses security issues, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
